# Create New Documentation Page Entry

**Page:** `[% page_name %]`

The documentation page you requested does not exist in the system configuration. As an administrator, you can create a new entry for this page.

## Page Information

- **Page Name:** [% page_name %]
- **Suggested Path:** Documentation/[% page_name %].md
- **Current Status:** Not configured

## Create Page Entry

Please fill out the following form to create a new documentation page entry:

<form method="post" action="[% c.uri_for_action('Documentation/edit_roles', [url_page_name]) %]">
    <input type="hidden" name="action" value="create_page_entry">
    
    <div class="form-group">
        <label for="description">Page Description:</label>
        <input type="text" id="description" name="description" value="[% suggested_description %]" class="form-control" required>
        <small class="form-text text-muted">A brief description of what this documentation page covers.</small>
    </div>

    <div class="form-group">
        <label for="site">Site Access:</label>
        <select id="site" name="site" class="form-control">
            [% FOR site IN available_sites %]
                <option value="[% site %]"[% IF site == suggested_site %] selected[% END %]>[% site %]</option>
            [% END %]
        </select>
        <small class="form-text text-muted">Which site(s) should have access to this documentation.</small>
    </div>

    <div class="form-group">
        <label>Required Roles:</label>
        <div class="checkbox-group">
            [% FOR role IN available_roles %]
                <div class="checkbox">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox" name="roles" value="[% role %]"[% IF suggested_roles.grep(role).size > 0 %] checked[% END %]>
                        [% role FILTER ucfirst %]
                    </label>
                </div>
            [% END %]
        </div>
        <small class="form-text text-muted">Select which roles should have access to this documentation page.</small>
    </div>

    <div class="form-actions">
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Create Page Entry</button>
        <a href="[% c.uri_for('/Documentation') %]" class="btn btn-secondary">Cancel</a>
    </div>
</form>

## What This Does

Creating a page entry will:

1. **Register the page** in the system so it appears in documentation listings
2. **Set access permissions** based on the roles you select
3. **Enable role editing** for this page in the future
4. **Allow the page to be viewed** by users with the appropriate roles

## Important Notes

- This only creates the **configuration entry** for the page
- The actual documentation file at `Documentation/[% page_name %].md` may or may not exist
- If the file doesn't exist, users will see an error when trying to view the page content
- You may need to create the actual documentation file separately

---

*This form is only available to administrators.*